      • Builder

        public Builder(javax.servlet.ServletContext servletContext,
               ObjectWrapper objectWrapper)
        Constructs a Builder with ServletContext and ObjectWrapper.
        Parameters:
        servletContext - ServletContext instance
        objectWrapper - the ObjectWrapper used when building the JSP tag library TemplateHashModel-s from the TLD-s. Usually, it should be the same ObjectWrapper that will be used inside the templates. null value is only supported for backward compatibility. For custom EL functions to be exposed, it must be non-null and an intanceof DefaultObjectWrapper (like typically, a DefaultObjectWrapper).

      • setMetaInfTldSources

        public void setMetaInfTldSources(List<? extends TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource> metaInfTldSources)
        Sets the list of places where we will look for META-INF/**/*.tld files. By default this is a list that only contains TaglibFactory.WebInfPerLibJarMetaInfTldSource.INSTANCE. This corresponds to the behavior that the JSP specification describes. See the TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource subclasses for the possible values and their meanings.

        This is usually set via the init-params of FreemarkerServlet.

        Parameters:
        metaInfTldSources - The list of TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource subclass instances. Their order matters if multiple TLD-s define a taglib with the same taglib-uri. In that case, the one found by the earlier TaglibFactory.MetaInfTldSource wins.
        See Also:
        setClasspathTlds(List)

      • setClasspathTlds

        public void setClasspathTlds(List<String> classpathTlds)
        Sets the class-loader resource paths of the TLD-s that aren't inside the locations covered by setMetaInfTldSources(List), yet you want them to be discovered. They will be loaded with the class loader provided by the servlet container.

        This is usually set via the init-params of FreemarkerServlet.

        Parameters:
        classpathTlds - List of String-s, maybe null. Each item is a resource path, like "/META-INF/my.tld". (Relative resource paths will be interpreted as root-relative.)
        See Also:
        setMetaInfTldSources(List)

      • build

        public TaglibFactory build()
                    throws ConfigurationException
        Description copied from interface: CommonBuilder
        Creates an instance of the product class. This is usually a new instance, though if the product is stateless, it's possibly a shared object instead of a new one. Builders shouldn't allow calling this method for multiple times (not counting calls that threw exceptions), and should throw IllegalStateException to prevent that.
        Specified by:
        build in interface CommonBuilder<TaglibFactory>
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException
